@startuml state-user-lifecycle
title trawhile — User Lifecycle

[*] --> Pending : System Admin\ncreates invitation record;\nusers row created\n(SR-007)

Pending --> Pending : expiry extended\n(SR-007a)

Pending --> Active : OIDC login matches\npending email;\nGDPR notice acknowledged;\nuser_profile created\n(SR-008, SR-057a)

state Active {
    Active : tracks time, views reports,\nmanages account, uses MCP
}

Pending --> ReadyForScrubbing : invitation expires\nor is cancelled\n(SR-009, SR-009a)

Active --> ReadyForScrubbing : user self-anonymises\n(SR-047) or System Admin\nremoves user (SR-010)

state "Ready for Scrubbing" as ReadyForScrubbing {
    ReadyForScrubbing : entry / stop active tracking session
    ReadyForScrubbing : entry / delete node_authorizations
    ReadyForScrubbing : entry / delete pending_invitations (if exists)
    ReadyForScrubbing : entry / delete user_profile (if exists;\n  cascade: user_oauth_providers, quick_access)
    ReadyForScrubbing : entry / revoke active mcp_tokens
    ReadyForScrubbing : [users row + time_entries (0..n) remain]
}

note right of ReadyForScrubbing
  Exits as soon as time_entries = 0.
  Immediate for pending users (no entries possible).
  May wait for F8.3 purge for anonymised users.
end note

ReadyForScrubbing --> [*] : users row deleted

@enduml
